This plugin is a thin wrapper around Handy, an external offline
speech-to-text application:

  https://github.com/cjpais/Handy
  Copyright (c) 2025 CJ Pais (MIT)

This plugin does **not** bundle, redistribute, or modify Handy. At
runtime the plugin downloads `Handy.AppImage` directly from CJ Pais'
GitHub Releases for the user's own machine (see `backend.ts`,
`HANDY_RELEASES_API`). The downloaded AppImage remains the property of
its authors and is governed by Handy's own MIT license; consult Handy's
LICENSE inside the AppImage for the canonical terms.

This plugin's source code (UI, configuration management, lifecycle) was
written independently from scratch; no source code from Handy was copied
or transliterated. The interfaces named `HandyConfig`, `HandyStatus`,
and `HandySettings` in this plugin describe the *shape of data we read
from Handy at runtime* — they are interoperability declarations, not
copies of Handy's own type definitions.
